# No Confidential Information

This repository is intended to be published to GitHub and served from GitHub Pages. Treat all committed files as public.

When building PoCs:

- Use mock, anonymized, or synthetic data only.
- Do not add real customer names, emails, tenant IDs, account IDs, tokens, API keys, passwords, certificates, private URLs, internal hostnames, or production incident details.
- Do not commit `.env` files, credentials, exported logs, private screenshots, or downloaded reports.
- If sample identifiers are needed, use obvious fake values like `team-alpha`, `service-demo`, `example.com`, or `00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000`.
- Keep secrets in local environment variables, GitHub repository secrets, or the target platform secret store, never in source files.
- Before adding a new PoC, check that fixtures, screenshots, README examples, and comments do not reveal internal or confidential information.

If a PoC needs realistic-looking operational data, create representative mock data instead of copying real monitoring, incident, or service data.
